## Conversation
User wants to move weave/trace_server/ (the server) into the `core` repo, restructured
into interface/ (contract), shared/ (impl-shared utils), sqlite_trace_server/,
clickhouse_trace_server/, and give the CLIENT (weave/) its own trace_server_interface.
Directives: use gt to build the stack locally; DO NOT push; "don't worry about
backcompat, focus on moving files into the correct spot first"; resolve open questions
via the grill-me skill.

Grill resolved (decision tree):
1. Clean move, fresh on andrew/move-trace-server-to-core-v1, NO shims. Prior shim-based
   ts-* stack (ts-server-interface->ts-impl-dirs->ts-move-impls->ts-ch-data, + ts-sqlite-impl)
   is reference-only.
2. Full client decoupling IS in scope, done FACADE-FIRST (this commit) so the ~169 client
   sites are repointed ONCE, then server reorg happens behind the facade.
3. Errors: server-raised errors stay SERVER-SIDE, NOT in the facade. Client keeps importing
   them directly from weave.trace_server.errors in local-in-process-server paths
   (transitional). Future: wire-level error-type discriminator -> client reconstructs.
   "For now keep it separate." Purely-client errors live client-side (already do).

