## Errors & Mistakes
- Codemod exclusion bug: first version used str.startswith('weave/trace_server'), which
  ALSO excluded weave/trace_server_bindings/ (shares the prefix). Bindings weren't
  repointed. Fixed to a Path.parents membership check; re-ran (idempotent) -> bindings done.
- saved_view facade: `from ...saved_view import *` did NOT export Column/Pin because
  saved_view.py defines `__all__ = ["SavedView"]`. Star import respects __all__. Fixed that
  one facade file to explicitly re-export Column, Pin, SavedView. (Only comparison_view,
  saved_view, test_only_example define __all__ among contract modules; only saved_view is
  client-facing.)
- ruff invoked with an unquoted $FILES list hit a spurious 'File name too long (os error 63)'
  on weave/utils/retry.py and aborted mid-list, leaving 12 files unfixed. Re-ran scoped via
  `xargs ruff` reading a file list -> all 12 import-order fixes applied, clean.

